revision.text:
During the Parade of Nations portion of the [[1964 Summer Olympics]] opening ceremony, athletes from each country participating in the Olympics paraded in the arena, preceded by their flag. The flag was borne by a sportsperson from that country chosen either by the [[National Olympic Committee]] or by the athletes themselves to represent their country. Although the Games were held in [[Japan]], [[English language|English]] was used to organize the Parade of Nations instead of [[Japanese language|Japanese]]. Had the parade followed the [[Japanese writing system|Japanese characters]], Greece would have been followed by Iceland, and Rhodesia would have been the penultimate country before [[Japan at the 1964 Summer Olympics|Japan]].
