'''Daniel Kaufman''' has founded or co-founded more than a dozen start-up companies. He has been working in the field of software and hardware for over 20 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/person/daniel-kaufman|title=Dan Kaufman - Partner @ Kaufman Organization {{!}} Crunchbase|website=Crunchbase|language=en|access-date=2017-12-08}}</ref>

He currently lives in [[New York City]], and continues to work with the internet radio start-ups [[Jango (website)|Jango]] and Radioairplay.com. He is also the founder of the cryptocurrency [[NeuCoin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/02/03/neucoin-raises-2-5m-to-be-a-headache-free-take-on-bitcoin/|title=NeuCoin raises $2.25M to be a headache-free take on Bitcoin|date=3 February 2015|publisher=Venture Beat|accessdate=22 July 2017|author=Ruth Reader}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hatch.mobi/news/2016/3/19/nd8p05mfydrksnlnwggwu5bo92t4q9|title=Daniel Kaufman and NeuCoin Team With Tech's Top Executives To Bring Cryptocurrency To The Masses|work=Hatch|access-date=2017-12-08|language=en-US}}</ref>

