'''Dewi Sandra Killick''' (born 3 April 1980) is an Indonesian singer, dancer, actress and model.

==Biography==
Sandra was born in Brazil on 3 April 1980.{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Dewi Sandra}} She is of [[Indo people|mixed heritage]]; her father, John George Killick, was a British national and her mother, Hajjah Prihartini, was [[Betawi people|Betawi]].{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Dewi Sandra}}{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}}{{sfn|Edmond 2008, Dewi Sandra}} As a child, she was overweight; this led her to receive the nickname "Miss Piggy".{{sfn|Edmond 2010, 'I Never say}} However, she lost weight and began modeling in her teens, later recording the [[compilation album]] ''Menari-Nari'' (''Dance'') with her fellow models.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}}

She released her first solo album, ''Kurasakan'' (''I Feel''), in 1998 to lukewarm reception. Critics objected that she was only "selling a pretty face". She then received further vocal training,{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}} after which she released ''Tak Ingin Lagi'' (''Don't Want It Anymore''), which was received better.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}}

Her next album, ''Kuakui'' (''I Admit''), was released in 2004 after three years production. The following album, 2007's ''Star'', was more experimental. It mixed uptempo beats on some tracks with slow ballads.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}}

The following year, Sandra became the host of the [[Indonesian Idol#Season 5|fifth season of ''Indonesian Idol'']]. She also turned to acting, starring in several teen films.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}}

Sandra released her fifth album, ''Wanita'' (''Woman''), not long after her divorce in 2009. A single from the album, "Kapan Lagi Bilang I Love You" ("When Will You Say I Love You Again"), was released in April, with the album following in October.{{sfn|KapanLagi.com, Dewi Sandra}} One of the songs, "Satu Untuk Selamanya", discussed how happy she had been with [[Glenn Fredly]] at the beginning of their relationship.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}}

In 2011 she was cast in her first ''sinetron'' (Indonesian soap opera), ''Nada Cinta'' (''Tones of Love''), as a singing teacher. She expressed surprise at the rushed nature of the filming.{{sfn|The Jakarta Post 2011, Dewi Sandra astounded}}

==Style==
Her first four albums were categorized with "bouncy R&B songs infused with a joyful mood". However, her fifth album, ''Wanita'', featured more melancholic melodies.{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}}

==Personal life==
She married actor [[Surya Saputra]] in the early 2000s; they divorced in 2005.{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}} She then married singer [[Glenn Fredly]]. He proposed to her at the [[Monas|National Monument]] and they were married in [[Bali]]{{sfn|Emond 2008, Dewi Sandra}} on her 26th birthday. But that [[interfaith marriage]], does not last long Fredly initiated divorce proceedings in April 2009.{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}} On 11 December 2011 Dewi Sandra married for third time, to Agus Rahman.{{sfn|The Jakarta Post 2011, Singer Dewi Sandra}}

She enjoys reading, becoming addicted to it after being introduced to the ''[[Harry Potter]]'' series as a teenager.{{sfn|Emond 2008, Dewi Sandra}} She also enjoys watching movies and travelling.{{sfn|Emond 2010, 'I Never say}}

Sandra admires [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Oprah Winfrey]], and [[Nelson Mandela]]; Madonna and Oprah for being strong, emancipated women, and Mandela for being a dedicated leader.{{sfn|Edmond 2010, 'I Never say}}

==Awards and accolades==
From 1999 to 2004, Sandra won the Panasonic Award for Best Female Presenter.{{sfn|TokohIndonesia.com, Dewi Sandra}} In 2001, she received the [[Anugerah Musik Indonesia|Indonesian Music Award]] for Best R&B Album. ''[[For Him Magazine|For Him Magazine Indonesia]]'' selected Sandra as the Sexiest Female Indonesian Artist and listed her seventh on their list of the sexiest women in the world in 2004.{{sfn|Kuswandini 2009, Dewi Sandra: Standing}}

