'''Hans Karl Wilhelm Max Heinrich Sellschopp''' (16 April 1891, in [[Schwerin]] -  5 August 1978 in [[Bottighofen]]) was a German businessman and [[Nazi]] cultural officer at the [[Reichsmusikkammer]], who worked as a concert promoter at [[Coventry Cathedral]] after [[World War II]]. He was later made [[Commander (order)|Grand Commander]] of the [[Order of the Crown of Italy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Eine Generation von Nachkommen |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006100233/http://sellschopp.org/strempel/nachkommen.php?id=La%205 |date=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Fricke |first1=Dr. Thomas |title=Landesarchiv Baden-Württemberg, Abt. Staatsarchiv Freiburg - Findbuch D 180/2: Spruchkammer Südbaden: DNZ-Akten - Strukturansicht |url=http://www.landesarchiv-bw.de/plink/?f=5-575371 |website=www.landesarchiv-bw.de}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Prieberg |first1=Fred K. |title=Trial of strength: Wilhelm Furtwängler in the Third Reich |date=1994 |publisher=Northeastern University Press |url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=p00IAQAAMAAJ&q=Hans+Sellschopp&dq=Hans+Sellschopp&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjH9N6M3ardAhUMo48KHdD2AskQ6AEIODAD |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Lübecker Schulen im "Dritten Reich" von Jörg Fligge {{!}} ISBN 978-3-7950-5214-0 {{!}} Fachbuch online kaufen - Lehmanns.de |url=https://www.lehmanns.de/shop/geisteswissenschaften/29740270-9783795052140-luebecker-schulen-im-dritten-reich |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Klee {{!}} Das Kulturlexikon zum Dritten Reich {{!}} 2009 |url=http://www.beck-shop.de/klee-kulturlexikon-dritten-reich/productview.aspx?product=433142 |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=argus.bstu.bundesarchiv|url=http://www.argus.bstu.bundesarchiv.de/R55-347/index.htm?kid=93ec0178-dc84-4af1-8fea-26e7efe30289 |website=www.argus.bstu.bundesarchiv.de}}</ref>

